blog.name: the-bespoke-psychopath
blog.title: Isengard on Gallifrey: S.A. Scully can see you now
blog.description:
22. American. Enlisted. Five descriptors to describe me would be: 
-weird
-short
-fangirl 
-curious 
-hungry 
-sarcastic
-smart-ass
Whoops. That's seven. Not five.
Anyway.
I'm part of too many Fandoms to keep track of and am easily distracted and entertained. I like to know a lot about everything and love being right because I'm never wrong. Usually. 30% of the time I am right 100% of the time.  Call me Lilly, and observe the awesome that is my tumblr, aka the distraction from the work I am probably supposed to be doing.
Don't be afraid. Contrary to what my friends will tell you, I bite only when hungry, and have had all of my shots.

tags: be warned if this one gets any hate
summary: I was the person who received David Tennant’s resignation. And Matt Smith’s resignation. And Peter Capaldi’s resignation. There...
text: I was the person who received David Tennant’s resignation. And Matt Smith’s resignation. And Peter Capaldi’s resignation. There should be some sort of special therapy for a grown-up Doctor Who fan whose heroes resign to him. I don’t want any more Doctors to quit. It’s terrifying. It’s like Santa saying, “I’ve had enough!” “No, Santa, that’s terrible – come back.”
source: Steven Moffat. Source: Fairford Festival of Fiction

reblog.comment: Steven Moffat. Source: Fairford Festival of Fiction
